    "created_at": "2014-07-02T19:59:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-02T19:59:13Z",
    "body": "The phenomena you're seeing here is that `extern crate std` is injected at the top of every crate, so the _crate root_ has the name `std` in scope by default. When you move it to a different module you enter a different namespace, so you'd have to import `std` again via `use std;`\n",
