    "updated_at": "2014-07-04T13:11:57Z",
    "body": "I sort of think we should always put `extern crate` symbols in the top-level scope, and only them, and put the crate root into an implicit scope (maybe addressable as `::crate`, and injecting `use ::crate::*` into every module...) below that, so the experience would be consistent between code in the crate root and code in a module, but I guess that gain in consistency might not be worth rejuggling everything and introducing more subtleties, and the impact on intra-crate `use` items makes it a nonstarter.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
